author: Timothy Puko
title: Natural Gas Inches Up, Helped by Room in Storage
text:
Natural gas prices are making small gains for a second-straight session thanks to smaller-than-expected additions to stockpiles, analysts said.
Natural gas futures for October delivery recently gained 1.8 cents, or 0.7%, to $2.701 a million British thermal units on the New York Mercantile Exchange. Despite the gains, prices--already in a narrow range for months--are still stuck in an even narrower range of 11 cents that they have...
